{"id":161,"parent_id":0,"book_id":8,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":161,"title":"Barnabas","subtitle":"","short_title":"Barnabas","uri":"/scriptures/bd/barnabas","content":[["div",{"id":"t1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/barnabas.t1","order":".000.443"},[".title","Barnabas"],["div",{"id":"p1","uri":"/scriptures/bd/barnabas.p1","order":".000.444"},["i","Son of consolation."],"A name given to Joseph, a Levite of Cyprus, who sold his possessions and gave the proceeds to the Apostles (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/4.36-37"},"Acts 4:36–37"],"); was of service to Saul after his conversion (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/9.27"},"9:27"],"); was sent by the Apostles to Antioch, where he worked with Saul (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/11.22-30"},"11:22–30"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/12.25"},"12:25"],"); with Paul on missionary journey (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/13?span=13-14"},"Acts 13–14"],"); and at Jerusalem (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/15"},"Acts 15"],"); they parted (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/15.39"},"15:39"],"). See also",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/1-cor/9.6"},"1 Cor. 9:6"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/gal/2.1,9,13"},"Gal. 2:1, 9, 13"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/col/4.10"},"Col. 4:10"],". Though not one of the Twelve, he was regarded as an Apostle (",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/acts/14.4,14"},"Acts 14:4, 14"],")."]]],"refs":null}
